[start section id="$final"]
Final Diagnosis
A.	Rectum, sigmoid, ascending, cecum and appendix, completion colectomy:  Residual invasive grade 3 (of 4) adenocarcinoma  located 7.8 cm from dentate line with associated prior biopsy site changes.  The tumor invades superficially into submucosa.  There are multiple (2) tubular adenomas with low grade dysplasia located in sigmoid and the ascending colon.  Anastomosis intact.  The appendix is unremarkable.  The proximal and distal margins are negative for tumor.  Multiple (17) lymph nodes are negative for tumor.

With available surgical materials, [AJCC (7th edition) pT1N0].

Seen in consultation with Dr. Jesse T. Rose.



[end section id="$final"]
[start section id="$gross"]

Gross Description
A.	Received fresh labeled left colon and rectum is a 6.0 cm long segment of ileum, a 15.0 cm long segment of cecum and ascending colon anastomosed to a 30.0 cm long segment of sigmoid, rectum and anus.  There is a 2.5 x 1.2 cm ulcerated area 10.0 cm from the anus and 7.8 cm from the anal verge.  There is a 5.2 x 0.9 cm appendix present.  Multiple lymph nodes are present.  Grossed by KIRKLAND.



Frozen Sect-Intraop
A.	Rectum, sigmoid, ascending, cecum and appendix, completion colectomy:  Residual invasive carcinoma and tubular adenomas (sigmoid/ascending colon).  HOLD to process lymph nodes and additional sections.

Frozen section histologic interpretation performed by:  Marion K. Ryan, M.D.





